For each of the following hardware specification and software configuration, state how many bits are needed for a) Virtual address, b) Physical address, c) Virtual page number, d) Physical page number, e) Offset
32-bit operating system, 4-KB pages, 1 GB of RAM
32-bit operating system, 16-KB pages, 2 GB of RAM
64-bit operating system, 16-KB pages, 16 GB of RAM
Note: you need to show the calculation to get full credits 
Note2: you need to show 15 numbers
Key concepts: page, virtual and physical address format

Calculations:
Virtual address bits = given by the OS/address-space size
Physical address bits = log2
offset bits = log 2
VPN = Virtual address bits - offset bits
PFN = bits Physical address bits - Offset bits
	​


1. 32 bit operating system, 4-kb pages, 1 gb of ram

a) Virtual address = 32 bits
b) Page size = 4KB = 4096 bytes = 2^12
  Physical Address = 30 bits
c) Virtual page number(VPN) = 32 - 12 = 20 bits 
d) Physical page number (PFN) = 18 bits
e) offset = 12 bits

2. 32-bit operating system, 16-KB pages, 2 GB of RAM

a) Virtual address bits  = 32
b) page size 16 KB = 16384 bytes = 2^14 
  Ram = 2 GB = 2^31 = Physical Adress = 31 bits
c) VPN = 32 - 14 = 18 bits
d) PFN = 31 - 14 = 17 bits

3. 64-bit operating system, 16-KB pages, 16 GB of RAM
  a) Virtual address = 64 
  b) Ram = 16 gb = 2^34 = Physical address = 34 bits
  c) VPN = 64 - 14 = 50 bits
  d) 34 - 14 = 20 bits
